so this is interesting.  the latest spacy installs just fine, but the version in medacy setup has issues (independent of medacy).  This issue can probably be closed out, the solution may lie here:

https://github.com/explosion/spaCy/issues/2441

I will take a look and bump the requirements version if all tests pass and
everything checks out.

In the mean time, you can clone down the repo, change the spaCy version in
the setup.py locally, and installed the package from your altered clone.

You should have no issue utilizing the actual package with the different
spaCy version as medaCy relies only on the core text processing
functionality and API of spaCy. These should be invariant under minor
releases.

Let me know if you run into any problems. Thanks!
